WARRI â€“ Local Government delegate congresses to elect one National delegate per LGA has held in Delta State with Chief Eddie Ono-Sorhue emerging National Delegate to represent Udu Local Government Area of the state in the forth-coming National Convention of the Peoples Democratic Party where the presidential flag-bearer of the party would be elected. Chief Ono-Sorhue, a former Chairman of Okpe and Udu local government councils was returned unopposed on Tuesday at the council headquarters, Otor-Udu following a general consensus from the party members and statutory delegates at the party meeting presided over by the LGA Chairman, Evang. David Siloko, who charged party faithful to be committed to the progress of the party for a prosperous future. Besides Chief Sorhue, another delegate elected was Obruche Omo Isaac as Person Living with disabilities. -Advertisement- Also in Ughelli North Local Government Area, the election which held at the party secretariat in Ughelli town saw former secretary of the Delta State Oil Producing Area Development Commission, DESOPADEC, Chief A.K Osawota emerging National Delegate for the LGA. Chief A.K Osawota was also elected on consensus basis as the position was earlier zoned to State Constituency 1 of the local government area and eventually, the leaders, delegates and stakeholders settled for the candidature of A.K Osawota who was thereafter declared winner. Addressing newsmen shortly after the meeting at Otor-Udu, Chief Eddie Ono-Sorhue thanked the party members, officials and leaders for the peaceful conduct of the exercise, noting that he would represent the interest of Udu at the National Convention so that an election-winning candidate could emerge from the convention in the best interest of the PDP and Nigeria in general. Results from other LGA were still being expected as at the time of filling the report.